page.title: 01Physical Features of D_Block
page.content: The{ D-block }is an area of rugged country of mainly{granite structure which has two complete communities and part of the community of an adjoining block.Over the years the region between the communities has decreased as housing and light industry has extented along the main roadways. The main community in the block is the town of{Penryn,}an old established borough,and a smaller village to the west{,Mabe. The south west corner of the block encompasses the north-west corner of {Falmouth,}and an area of commence and industry between, known as{Ponsharden. The land is hilly and slopes into a valley in the south-west and the tidal creek to the east.{ }
